Halve the tomatoes. Peel the @sweet potatoes{12%ounce}, then dice into ½-inch cubes. Halve, peel, and mince half the @yellow onion{1}. Peel, then mince or grate the @ginger{1%thumb}.

Heat @olive oil{2%tablespoons} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onions and ginger and cook, tossing for ~{4-5%minutes}, until soft.

Add the @brown rice{3/4%cup} to the pan and cook, stirring for ~{1%minute}. Add the @white wine vinegar{2%tablespoon} and @paprika{1%teaspoon} and simmer for ~{2%minutes}, until the liquid has reduced slightly.

Add @water{2 1/2%cups}, the @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and the diced sweet potato to the pan. Bring to a boil, then reduce to simmer for ~{20-25%minutes} until the rice is tender.

> TIP: If the liquid reduces before the rice and sweet potato are tender, simply add a splash of water to the pan.

Stir the @edamame{1.5%ounce} into the rice, cover, and let stand ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, toss the @spinach{5%ounce} and @grape tomatoes{4%ounce}(halved) in a large #bowl{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Finish and plate: Divide the spinach and tomato salad between plates (or bowls!) and serve the rice mixture on top. Sprinkle with the @sunflower seeds{1%ounce}, @feta cheese{2%ounce}, and dig in!